items.title: Tatas to collaborate in defence 'wherever there is scope', says chairman N Chandra during visit to Solar Industries' factory
items.description: Chandrasekaran reviewed Solar Industries' capabilities, missile and other defence production facilities during his visit. The Tata Group has been actively participating in defence programmes of strategic importance with the Ministry of Defence (MoD) as well as Defence Research and Development Organization (DRDO).

items.title: Explainer: Why personal Wills are leading to succession disputes in India Inc?
items.description: Following the death of business leader Sunjay Kapur, a legal dispute emerged over his assets, with his children from first marriage to actress Karisma Kapoor challenging a Will presented by his widow, Priya Sachdev.

items.title: Trump's tariffs bite off Rs 25,000 crore from shrimp exporters' profit, Andhra CM Chandrababu Naidu seeks Centre's help
items.description: Andhra CM Chandrababu Naidu has called for a Rs 100 crore corpus fund, cold storages, and seafood markets, adding that the the state is ready to set up a shrimp producers' committee to ensure farm-to-market supply chains.
